NetVision Says Smile Purchase by Partner Communications May Hurt Company

-- B y   G w e n   A c k e r m a n
-- 
2011-03-02T07:26:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-02/netvision-says-smile-purchase-by-partner-communications-may-hurt-company.html
  NetVision Ltd . said the regulator’s
approval of Partner Communications Ltd.’s acquisition of 012
Smile Telecom Ltd. may negatively affect its competitive
standing in the market and its financial results. The company
said, in a statement to the Tel Aviv Stock Exchange today, that
new regulations may also allow it to change its business
relationship with Cellcom Israel Ltd. Both Netvision and Cellcom
are owned by IDB Holding Corp.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gwen Ackerman in Jerusalem at 
 gackerman@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alisa Odenheimer at 
 aodenheimer@bloomberg.net  